      "The works council engagement process for Germany has not yet begun",
      "Deductions include at minimum: tax withholding (employees), platform/service fees (contractors), and benefits (employees where applicable)"
    ]
  },

  "escalations": [
    {
      "type": "ambiguity",
      "description": "'Real time' is undefined. It could mean instant per-delivery update, periodic refresh (every N minutes), or available-by-end-of-shift. California wage statement law requires specific pay period timing but does not mandate real-time display. The freshness SLA fundamentally affects architecture (event-driven vs. polling vs. batch) and cost.",
      "affected_stakeholders": ["Product/Engineering", "Drivers (all markets)", "Finance/Payroll"],
      "options": [
        "Per-delivery: earnings update within seconds of delivery completion",
        "Near-real-time: earnings update within 15 minutes via periodic aggregation",
        "Session-based: earnings snapshot refreshed each time the driver opens the view"
      ],
      "recommendation": "Define 'real time' as per-delivery update within 60 seconds of delivery completion. This meets driver expectations without requiring sub-second event streaming infrastructure."
    },
    {
      "type": "ambiguity",
      "description": "'Deductions' is not defined. The nature and number of deduction categories differ radically by jurisdiction and classification. California employees may have tax withholding, benefits premiums, and garnishments. Indonesian contractors may have platform service fees. Without a defined taxonomy, the feature cannot be built correctly.",
      "affected_stakeholders": ["Drivers (all markets)", "Legal/Compliance Team", "Finance/Payroll"],
      "options": [
        "Define a fixed global deduction taxonomy with jurisdiction-specific subsets",
        "Allow each jurisdiction to define its own deduction categories dynamically",
        "Start with a minimal set (tax, platform fees, benefits) and expand per jurisdiction"
      ],
      "recommendation": "Define a jurisdiction-specific deduction taxonomy managed as configuration, not code. Start with the legally required categories per market and allow the compliance team to add categories without engineering changes."
    },
    {
      "type": "ambiguity",
      "description": "'Base pay' meaning is unclear for Indonesian independent contractors. Contractors typically do not receive 'base pay' — they earn per-task. If the feature forces a 'base pay' line item for contractors, it could imply an employment relationship and create misclassification risk. If omitted, the four-component breakdown is inconsistent across markets.",
      "affected_stakeholders": ["Drivers (Indonesia)", "Legal/Compliance Team", "Product/Engineering"],
      "options": [
        "Show 'base pay' as zero or N/A for contractors",
        "Replace 'base pay' with a contractor-appropriate equivalent like 'minimum task fee'",
        "Remove 'base pay' from contractor views entirely and accept asymmetric breakdowns"
      ],
      "recommendation": "Remove 'base pay' from contractor views and replace with jurisdiction-appropriate compensation components. Asymmetric breakdowns are correct — forcing symmetry across classifications creates legal risk."
    }
  ],

  "rejection_reasons": []
}

